goals.question: What is the distribution of wildlife strikes by species?
goals.rationale: This helps identify the most common species involved in bird strikes and can inform mitigation strategies.

goals.question: What is the trend in bird strikes over time?
goals.rationale: This helps identify if there are any patterns or trends in bird strikes over time and can inform preventative measures.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?
goals.rationale: This helps identify which phases of flight are most susceptible to bird strikes and can inform preventative measures.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by aircraft make and model?
goals.rationale: This helps identify which aircraft are most susceptible to bird strikes and can inform preventative measures.

goals.question: What is the distribution of bird strikes by cost of damage?
goals.rationale: This helps identify the severity of bird strikes and can inform cost-benefit analyses of preventative measures.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    species_count = data['Wildlife_Species'].value_counts()
    ax = species_count.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(12, 6), color='c')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wildlife strikes by species?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wildlife Species')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Strikes')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(['Wildlife Strikes'])
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Flight_Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Flight_Date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['Flight_Date'])]
    data['Year'] = data['Flight_Date'].dt.year

    yearly_counts = data.groupby('Year').size()

    plt.plot(yearly_counts.index, yearly_counts.values)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Number of Bird Strikes')
    plt.title('What is the trend in bird strikes over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    phase_counts = data['Phase_of_flight'].value_counts()
    plt.pie(phase_counts, labels=phase_counts.index, autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by phase of flight?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(phase_counts.index, loc='upper left', bbox_to_anchor=(1, 0.5))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    aircraft_counts = data['Aircraft_Make_Model'].value_counts()
    aircraft_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 6), color='blue', legend=True)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of bird strikes by aircraft make and model?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel("Aircraft Make and Model")
    plt.ylabel("Number of Bird Strikes")
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['Cost_Total__'], bins=20, color='blue', edgecolor='black')
    plt.axvline(data['Cost_Total__'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['Cost_Total__'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Cost of Damage')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of bird strikes by cost of damage?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
